# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Best Hairline runs in two modes (see lib/demo/mode.ts):
#
#   DEMO  (default) — a self-contained wig storefront served by an embedded
#         mock. No backend, no Cimplify account. Push to Vercel as-is.
#         Triggered by ANY non-hosted key (mock-dev, blank, etc.).
#
#   REAL  — paste a hosted Cimplify public key below. The storefront then
#         pulls the client's live catalogue from Cimplify and the demo layer
#         switches off automatically.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Tenant public key. `mock-dev` (or blank) = DEMO mode with the embedded wig
# catalogue. A `cpk_live_*` / `cpk_test_*` key = REAL mode (hosted Cimplify).
NEXT_PUBLIC_CIMPLIFY_PUBLIC_KEY=mock-dev

# Optional hard override of the mode: 1 = force demo, 0 = force real.
# Leave unset to auto-detect from the key prefix above.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO=

# Optional. Forces a fixed canonical URL for sitemap.xml, robots.txt,
# OpenGraph, and llms.txt. Leave unset and the storefront derives the
# canonical from the request `Host` header automatically.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
